⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Maureen Johnson
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Maureen Johnson:H1:77bc7d⟧

WHO   — Maureen Johnson Smith, born 1882 in Missouri, a Howard Families daughter who married Brian Smith, bore the longest-lived of men, and lived long enough to tell her own story across two thousand years.
WHAT  — The narrator of To Sail Beyond the Sunset — wife, mother, lover, businesswoman, and at last time-traveller — Heinlein's most candid woman, mother of Lazarus and mistress of her own destiny.
WHERE — From rural Missouri and Kansas City of the early 1900s through a long American century — and out into the multiverse of the Circle of Ouroboros, reunited with Lazarus.
WHY   — Because a woman's life is hers to author; because love, sex, family, and freedom are not separate goods but one good; because she would sail beyond the sunset rather than settle for a smaller world.
HOW   — By a frank intelligence her century could not contain, by the Howard longevity she passed to her son, and at the end by rescue into the World as Myth, where the living and the fictional share one table.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A lady is a woman who makes a man behave like a gentleman — and never once forgets she is the one steering.

